          <xref ref="yawningContageousP1">Exercise</xref> describes an experiment by Myth Busters, where they examined whether a person yawning would affect whether others to yawn. The traditional belief is that yawning is contagious <mdash /> one yawn can lead to another yawn, which might lead to another, and so on. In that exercise, there was the option of selecting a one-sided or two-sided test. Which would you recommend (or which did you choose)? Justify your answer in 1-3 sentences.
